===Etymology===
Hebrew יִצְחָק (Yitzchak or Yitzhak), meaning "laughed; laughter" (since his mother [[Sarah]] laughed when told she was pregnant at her old age), Standard Hebrew Yiẓḥaq, Tiberian Hebrew Yiṣḥāq; Arabic اسحاق (ʾIsḥāq).

===Proper noun===
'''Isaac'''

#(''Bible'') the son and heir of [[Abraham]], father of [[Esau]] and [[Jacob]]
#{{given name|male|}} a male [[given name]]

